# Benchmark integrity

The preregistration's credibility is the project's most reputation-critical asset
(master doc §8.1). These rules exist so no agent can quietly damage it.

- The document is currently **DRAFT**. Sections later marked **FROZEN** are never edited —
  not for typos, not for formatting. Changes to frozen content happen only as numbered,
  append-only amendments per the document's §0 policy, and freezing itself is a human act
  (signed tag + external timestamp).
- **Never weaken a baseline** or its configuration so the proposed system wins (§8.3). The
  strongest baselines (B5 and the composite B5+B3+B6) must stay the primary comparison.
- **Never touch the falsification criterion** (§8.6-derived) except via a review-queue
  amendment. The pre-committed null on C1 is reported as prominently as any win.
- INVALID-run rules are fixed pre-run; INVALID runs are retained and marked, never deleted,
  and INVALID is never used as a post-hoc exclusion lever.
- The private held-out fault-seed split never enters this repository, agent context, or any
  committed file — only its commitment hash does (see the holdout section of the
  preregistration).

This rule's glob grows to cover fixture/result directories when they exist (M5+).
